changeBackground

  • changeBackground(__namedParameters: { color?: string; image?: string; scene: Scene }): void

  • Change the background by using either a color (given by a string) or an image URL

    example
    kepler.changeBackground( {scene, color: '#7777777'} )

    Parameters

    • __namedParameters: { color?: string; image?: string; scene: Scene }
      • Optional color?: string
      • Optional image?: string
      • scene: Scene

    Returns void

changeView

  • changeView(view: string, __namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: Controls; scene: Scene }): void

  • Change the view of the scene

    example
    kepler.changeView('north', controls)

    Parameters

    • view: string

      Possible values are up, down, east, west, north, south

    • __namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: Controls; scene: Scene }
      • camera: Camera
      • controls: Controls

        The Trackball controls

      • scene: Scene

    Returns void

fitScene

  • fitScene(__namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: TrackballControls; fitRatio?: number; scene?: any; selection?: Object3D[] | Object3D }): void

  • Fit a scene or a specific object or array of objects. The default value for the fitRatio is 1.2

    example
    threeExtra.fitScene( {scene, camera, controls} )

    Parameters

    • __namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: TrackballControls; fitRatio?: number; scene?: any; selection?: Object3D[] | Object3D }
      • camera: Camera
      • controls: TrackballControls
      • Optional fitRatio?: number
      • Optional scene?: any
      • Optional selection?: Object3D[] | Object3D

    Returns void

zoomToIntersection

  • zoomToIntersection(__namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: any; duration?: number; event: MouseEvent; scene: Object3D; zoomFactor?: number }): void

  • Zoom to the intersected point with animation (duration). If nothing is picked, the model is centered and unzoom until fitting the whole scene

    Parameters

    • __namedParameters: { camera: Camera; controls: any; duration?: number; event: MouseEvent; scene: Object3D; zoomFactor?: number }
      • camera: Camera
      • controls: any
      • Optional duration?: number
      • event: MouseEvent
      • scene: Object3D
      • Optional zoomFactor?: number

    Returns void
